## Spatial Relationships & Autocorrelation
K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN) graph will be built instead of a fixed-distance radius, which is not appropriate in Scotland because the Highlands are massive and sparse while Speyside is tiny and packed, thus, KNN guarantees that every distillery is evaluated against its closest peers.
*k = 4* as is used as  a standard baseline to generate a spatial weights matrix, and then run Global Moran's I tests.
# install.packages("spdep")
library(spdep)
# install.packages("spdep")
library(spdep)
# Extract geographic coordinates from the Projected CRS (British National Grid)
coords <- st_coordinates(whisky)
# Extract geographic coordinates from the Projected CRS (British National Grid)
